    .question
      %a{ name: 'what' }
      What is beCamp?
    .answer
      beCamp is Charlottesville's version of the
      = link_to 'BarCamp', 'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bar_camp', target: 'blank'
      unconference movement - a conference organized on the fly
      by attendees, for attendees.

    .question
      %a{ name: 'who' }
      Who attends beCamp?
    .answer
      You! Software developers, system administrators,
      quality assurance, devops, designers, business developers
      and anyone interested in technology.

    .question
      %a{ name: 'when'}
      When is beCamp?
    .answer
      beCamp begins Friday, October 23rd, 2015 at 5:00PM for topic organization.
      beCamp continues Saturday, October 24th, 2015 at 9:00AM for presentations.

    .question
      %a{ name: 'where' }
      Where is beCamp held?
    .answer
      beCamp is at a new location for 2015! The pitches and networking on Friday
      will be held at
      = link_to 'Portico', 'http://www.porticocville.org/', target: 'blank'
      in Charlottesville, VA.
      %br
      Saturday's presentations will be held at
      = link_to 'Studio IX', 'http://www.studioix.co/', target: 'blank'
      which is next door to Portico.
      %br
      =link_to 'Google Maps', 'https://www.google.com/maps/place/Studio+IX/@38.024074,-78.483263,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x27588bbcea2d8ed2', target: 'blank'

