      = link_to 'Brazos Tacos', 'http://brazostacos.com/', target: 'blank'
      is also near by!

    .question
      %a{ name: 'rules' }
      Are there rules?
    .answer
      beCamp draws people together from many backgrounds and experiences to
      learn and teach about technology.  While you are at beCamp, help foster
      a friendly environment.
      %ul
        %li be polite
        %li be kind
        %li be respectful
        %li be helpful
      At beCamp, we do not tolerate offensive comments about gender, age, sexual
      orientation, disability, physical appearance, race, or religion, or any
      inappropriate physical contact.  If a participant engages in harassing behavior,
      beCamp volunteers may take any action they deem appropriate, including warning
      the offender or expulsion from beCamp.  Any participant who has a concern should
      bring it immediately to the beCamp organizer.

    .question
      %a{ name: 'tbd' }
      Why is the schedule TBD?
    .answer
      The schedule will be made Friday night by attendees.

    .question
      %a{ name: 'topic' }
      How are topics decided?
    .answer
      On Friday evening, anyone in attendance can suggest
      topics for sessions held the following day. The
      suggester indicates whether it is a topic they'd like to
      present on, hold a group discussion on, or learn more about. After
      all the suggestions have been written down, they are placed on
      a wall and attendees mark the topics they are interested
      in. The suggestions that have the most votes are chosen as part of the
      conference schedule for the following day.

    .question
      %a{ name: 'lightning' }
      What about topics that are not chosen?
    .answer
      Topics that are not chosen for the main scheduling blocks
      can still be presented as a five minute "Lightning Talk"
      where presenters can share their message with the other
      conference attendees. This Lightning Talk portion is held
      Saturday around lunch time, and may include talks that were
      not pitched on Friday night.

    .question
      %a{ name: 'history' }
      How did beCamp get started?
    .answer
      The first beCamp was held in June 2007 when organizer
      Steve Stedman decided to hold a "summer camp for geeks."
